Latkes
via Michael Heumann

4 potatoes
1 onion
1/4 cup flour
1 egg
2 tsp baking powder
salt/pepper to taste
vegetable oil.  a lot.

Grate potatoes and onion in a food processor (or a cheese grater's finest side) and add other ingredients one by one.

Heat oil in a pan, about 1/4 inch deep (more or less).

Pour batter into small circles, let them get semi-solid, and them flip.  Store on a baking tray, alternated with brown paper from bags.  Keep in a heated oven.
